<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-2627AC38-117B-44C1-AD22-59CB29A2B34F" version="3" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-2627AC38-117B-44C1-AD22-59CB29A2B34F" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Install the embedded HTML TSM</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Tools</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><context id="CONTEXT_8EF3B1F09A6045C1B74B709625644461" class="- topic/section task/context "><p class="- topic/p ">This document describes the initial installation of the HTML TSM of this system on the controller. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Robin is used to install the TSM in this procedure. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">ORS is used to update the TSM 
</p></context><prereq id="PREREQ_018D2C0152F34CF4BABB47B5BABD53AE" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><ul id="UL_D60F589B6D7943B2AA7A9EB8E40E533F" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_49A70D7FE3524F928A4F9263CC6D798F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> You need a SAM key with valid licenses for this print system. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Licenses should include <ph varid="Adam" translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">ADAM</ph>, SDS and the TSM. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> ORS must be enabled and configured for the TSM to be updated 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="ORSSETUP001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-07BC7664-5AAE-4C27-A331-C2F6D4AB2349.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text How to set up Océ Remote Service?>How to set up On Remote Service (ORS)</xref> 
</p></li></ul></prereq><steps id="GUID-A658A112-D7C8-4E1B-9920-99DFF69E2CD1" class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Start <ph varid="Adam" translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">ADAM</ph> 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="Start_adam" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-685E6504-D43E-4063-96D4-B0A4F752A1F6.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text How to start ADAM?>How to start ADAM</xref> 
</p></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Tap the TSM button in the <ph varid="Adam" translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">ADAM</ph> screen. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">If there is no TSM available, select the [Tools] icon (gear icon). 
</p><fig id="GUID-E0E6283F-AC3F-4976-9C6C-6C124FBEAF16" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D038B436-7D55-4977-ABCE-E5358469FA32-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D038B436-7D55-4977-ABCE-E5358469FA32-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> After a few seconds a popup window will appear “Autoimport in progress” : the TSM will be automatically imported locally (this is a pure local action, connection to network is not needed) 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><note id="GUID-3C480307-A4DC-4744-B797-399B19FF0B3F" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">If the “Autoimport in progress does not appear after 5 minutes, go to Step 5 
</p></note><fig id="GUID-11588A26-2367-4B4F-831D-C9EAA6C5EF9C" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-853F5B2A-88DE-46AF-9687-2D700708A423-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-853F5B2A-88DE-46AF-9687-2D700708A423-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">As long as the popup window is displayed, the import action is on going, it is recommended to not change menu and to wait until the pop window disappears, 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When the popup window disappears, the following window appears and you can find the internal TSM just imported. 
</p><fig id="GUID-51855659-F4CF-4370-A2EE-C68B6BFAF03C" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D6BE8B9C-3BF6-481C-999E-A5EFE4E8DA32-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D6BE8B9C-3BF6-481C-999E-A5EFE4E8DA32-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">You can now go back to Porthos to open the TSM 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> If the popup window does not appear, click on “Import” button, you should see the available internal TSM, select it by touching the RED “O” button so that it becomes GREEN “I” 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="GUID-24ACCE01-FDA9-465A-8908-A425A7BB4A71" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C9F03DFC-DEEB-4F9C-937E-B785FA71A1F8-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C9F03DFC-DEEB-4F9C-937E-B785FA71A1F8-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-642913A8-9290-43DD-80CA-104BABCE6E59" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-03102531-6C69-42CA-815E-20CDD57C4A9D-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-03102531-6C69-42CA-815E-20CDD57C4A9D-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Then click on “Apply”, the following screen appears with a dynamic logo circle, this means that the TSM import is on going. : 
</p><fig id="GUID-9BA2F9A7-F632-4804-855F-C39C4C80C9D1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-9588261B-50CE-4B84-97C9-21398E54812A-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9588261B-50CE-4B84-97C9-21398E54812A-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> Wait until the following screen is displayed 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="GUID-E26DD232-6635-4AF3-BACD-07E73445E49B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-1A8D2B57-C871-476F-90D6-0A9BF997D569-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-1A8D2B57-C871-476F-90D6-0A9BF997D569-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">You can now go back to Porthos to open the TSM 
</cmd></step></steps></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-4998CEE3-DF0A-4501-ADA0-694495243747.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>HTML TSM on the Printer</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>